oid.name: PDSAllocatedObjectIdentifier
oid.description: An identifier allocated by the PDS for an instance of a type of updateable data item on the PDS which can occur more than once concurrently, e.g. name, address, telecom and related person. This identifier is allocated by the PDS after an instance of such data is first added on to the PDS. It can subsequently be retrieved from the PDS along with the specific instance to which it relates, and then used to identify that specific instance when altering or removing it.
